<br>
I confess that I am more of a Realist than Idealist when it comes to politics. However, I can't ignore moral issues at certain points, hence my political Realism is reigned in by my externalist moral view. Actions have meaning, and certain actions have moral meanings.<br>
<br>
In my view violent actions are not amoral. They carry moral meaning which are perspectival as you aptly point out. Osama bin Laden thinks of his Jihad as morally good. We the victims of his Jihad see it as morally bad. I am of the opinion that all sane people agree that violence in any form is morally wrong. However, people tend to loosely invoke the principle "the ends justify the means" to provide moral meaning to violent acts they seek to justify as a good.<br>
<br>
Going to War against the Axis powers was a necessity. The US had been attacked and war declared on it. The choice was clearly before us at that time: fight or lose our freedom. However, the USA is not presented with the same problem concerning Iraq. Indeed. Iraq has not declared war on the US and they haven't attacked our borders. Iraqi support of Osama's Jihad is not even close to Pearl Harbor. The US government can't justify an attack on Iraq as a moral good until they can clearly demonstrate that Iraq is a clear and present danger to US borders or to the borders of our NATO allies.<br>
<br>
In order to have the moral certitude that a US war against Iraq is a good we need to have the full support of the UN Security council. With their full support then we can be assured that war against Iraq is morally meaningfull. Without the support of the World and our allies there will is doubt that US action against Iraq is good; unless, of course, the US can clearly make it's case against Iraq. If the US can clearly demonstrate Iraq is a threat to the world, I doubt that the UN Security council would not support US action.<br>
<br>
At any rate, I will end here... my post is way too long. =) <p><HTML><IMG SRC="http://64.81.30.48/lurisig.jpg" HSPACE="150" WIDTH="330" HEIGHT="185" BORDER="0"> </HTML></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utrechdashadowknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trech Da ShadowKnight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 775<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/24/02 9:34:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The US government can't justify an attack on Iraq as a moral good until they can clearly demonstrate that Iraq is a clear and present danger to US borders or to the borders of our NATO allies.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
